---
import NairobiClock from "./nairobi-clock.astro";
---

<section class="colophon" id="colophon">
  <div class="wrap colo-grid">
    <div>
      <p class="chapter">Colophon</p>
      <h2>About me, briefly</h2>
      <p style="margin-top:18px">
        <b>I engage with the whole life cycle</b> — brainstorming, prototyping, building,
        refining — and I do my best work in cross-functional teams where ideas move
        freely.
      </p>
      <p>
        Before software, I facilitated ten-week public-health programs with the
        Kenya Red Cross for over a hundred young adults. Explaining complex
        things simply, to any audience, turned out to be the most transferable
        skill I own.
      </p>
      <p>
        Fintech sharpened it into a principle: <b
          >when people trust you with their savings, "mostly works" is not a
          standard.</b
        >
      </p>
    </div>
    <dl class="spec">
      <dt>Languages</dt>
      <dd>TypeScript · JavaScript · Python · Dart · Kotlin</dd>
      <dt>Frontend</dt>
      <dd>
        React · React Native · Next.js · Flutter · Svelte · Astro · Angular
      </dd>
      <dt>State &amp; data</dt>
      <dd>Django · Firebase · Supabase · Zustand · Redux · TanStack Query</dd>
      <dt>Education</dt>
      <dd>BSc, Machakos University · 2020</dd>
      <dt>Base</dt>
      <dd>Nairobi, Kenya · UTC+3 · <NairobiClock /> local</dd>
      <dt>This site</dt>
      <dd>Bespoke, naturally. I wouldn't hand you anything less.</dd>
    </dl>
  </div>

  <blockquote class="pull-quote wrap">
    <p class="pull-label">On the stack question</p>
    <p>
      I often get asked: "Do you work with React or Angular? React Native or
      Flutter?" My honest answer — it doesn't matter. These are tools, and tools
      can be learned. What can't be faked is the dedication to the end result:
      an experience your customers love and growth your business can measure.
      That's what I guarantee, regardless of the stack.
    </p>
  </blockquote>
</section>

<style>
  .colophon {
    padding: 84px 0;
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--color-border);
  }
  .colo-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 1.1fr 0.9fr;
    gap: 56px;
  }
  .colo-grid p {
    color: var(--color-text-muted);
    margin-bottom: 16px;
    max-width: 58ch;
  }
  .colo-grid p b {
    color: var(--color-text);
  }
  .spec {
    font-family: var(--mono);
    font-size: 13.5px;
  }
  .spec dt {
    color: var(--color-accent);
    font-size: 11px;
    letter-spacing: 0.12em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    margin-top: 18px;
  }
  .spec dd {
    margin: 6px 0 0;
    color: var(--color-text);
  }

  @media (max-width: 940px) {
    .colo-grid {
      grid-template-columns: 1fr;
      gap: 36px;
    }
  }

  .pull-quote {
    margin-top: 56px;
    padding-top: 40px;
    border-top: 1px solid var(--color-border);
  }
  .pull-label {
    font-family: var(--mono);
    font-size: 11px;
    letter-spacing: 0.12em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--color-accent-secondary);
    margin-bottom: 14px;
  }
  .pull-quote p:not(.pull-label) {
    font-family: var(--display);
    font-weight: 600;
    font-size: clamp(20px, 2.6vw, 28px);
    line-height: 1.4;
    letter-spacing: -0.01em;
    max-width: 50ch;
  }
</style>
